  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Moreover, the sons of Obededom,.... The same at whose house the ark was, before it was brought by David to Zion; his sons were porters also, as himself, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 15:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", mention is made of eight sons of his, according to their birth: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Shemaiah, Jehozabad, Joah, Sacar, Nethaneel, Ammiel, Issachar, Peulthai; for God blessed him; as with wealth and riches, so with a numerous offspring, and that because of his entertainment of the ark at his house; the great increase of his family is aggravated by the Jews (q) beyond all credit, that all in his family brought eight at a birth; the Targum here makes them eighty two in all. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(q) Hieron. Trad. Heb. in 2. Reg. fol. 77. M. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(q) Hieron. Trad. Heb. in 2. Reg. fol. 77. M. ",
            "children": []
